  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you know when you are going into the friendzone?",
  "response": "Identifying when you might be entering the \"friendzone\" can be nuanced and varies from person to person, but there are some common signs to look for:\n\n1. **Lack of Romantic Interest**: If the person frequently talks about other romantic interests or flirts with others in front of you without showing any romantic interest in you, it may indicate a platonic relationship.\n\n2. **Physical Boundaries**: If physical interaction is limited to friendly gestures (like hugs or high-fives) and there\u2019s little to no increase in intimacy (holding hands, cuddling, etc.), it could signal a non-romantic dynamic.\n\n3. **Consistent Group Activities**: If they often prefer hanging out in groups rather than one-on-one, or if they suggest activities that are more like friend outings than dates (e.g., movie nights at home vs. dinner at a romantic restaurant), it might suggest a non-romantic angle.\n\n4. **Clear Communication**: If they have mentioned wanting to keep things platonic or have expressed a desire to not complicate things, this is a definite sign.\n\n5. **Emotional Support Role**: If you find yourself in the role of the \"listener\" or \"support friend\" where they confide in you about their romantic problems or relationships without any reciprocation of feelings, it might indicate a friendzone situation.\n\n6. **Limited Flirting**: A lack of flirting or romantic teasing (especially if you've tried to initiate it) can suggest they're not looking to move the relationship beyond friendship.\n\n7. **Direct Questions**: Sometimes, direct questions about your feelings might come up. If they seem taken aback or uncomfortable with any hint of romantic interest you show, it could mean they're not on the same page.\n\n8. **Future Talk**: If they talk about future plans but don't include you in a romantic sense, or only reference you in a friend context, it might indicate a lack of romantic intention.\n\nUltimately, open and honest communication is key. If you're unsure of where you stand, consider discussing your feelings with the other person; this can clarify intentions and potentially shift the dynamic if both parties are interested.",
